    "faqs": [
      {
        "question": "Is MRI thigh painful?",
        "answer": "No. You simply lie still; the scan is painless.\n"
      },
      {
        "question": "How long does the scan take?",
        "answer": "20–45 minutes depending on whether contrast is used.\n"
      },
      {
        "question": "Can I eat before the scan?",
        "answer": "Yes, unless you are scheduled for a contrast-enhanced study—then fast 4 hours."
      },
      {
        "question": "When will I get my report?",
        "answer": "Most reports are ready within 2 hours; urgent cases within 30 minutes.\n"
      },
      {
        "question": "Is contrast dye always required?",
        "answer": "No. Only when infection, tumor or complex injury is suspected.\n"
      },
      {
        "question": " How much does an MRI of the thigh cost at Cadabams Diagnostics?",
        "answer": "The **cost of an MRI on thigh** can vary based on several factors, including whether contrast material is used and the specifics of your insurance coverage. For detailed pricing information regarding an **MRI Thigh** scan at Cadabams Diagnostics, please contact our billing department directly or visit our website. We can provide you with an estimate and discuss insurance and payment options. "
      }
    ],
